ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Scale of participant belief that pain was caused by physical activity, as part of the Fear-Avoidance Beliefs Questionnaire (FABQ).
Scale of participant belief that physical activity makes pain worse, as part of the Fear-Avoidance Beliefs Questionnaire (FABQ).
Scale of participant belief that physical activity might harm the back, as part of the Fear-Avoidance Beliefs Questionnaire (FABQ).
Scale of participant belief that they should not do physical activities which (might) make pain worse, as part of the Fear-Avoidance Beliefs Questionnaire (FABQ).
Scale of participant belief that they cannot do physical activities which (might) make pain worse, as part of the Fear-Avoidance Beliefs Questionnaire (FABQ).
Scale of participant belief that pain was caused by work or by an accident at work, as part of the Fear-Avoidance Beliefs Questionnaire (FABQ).
Scale of participant belief that pain was aggravated by work, as part of the Fear-Avoidance Beliefs Questionnaire (FABQ).
Scale of participant response to the statement, ''I have a claim for compensation for my pain,'' as part of the Fear-Avoidance Beliefs Questionnaire (FABQ).
Scale of participant belief that their work is too heavy, as part of the Fear-Avoidance Beliefs Questionnaire (FABQ).
Scale of participant belief that work makes or would make pain worse, as part of the Fear-Avoidance Beliefs Questionnaire (FABQ).
Scale of participant belief that work might harm their back, as part of the Fear-Avoidance Beliefs Questionnaire (FABQ).
Scale of participant belief that they should not do normal work with present pain, as part of the Fear-Avoidance Beliefs Questionnaire (FABQ).
Scale of participant belief that they cannot do normal work with present pain, as part of the Fear-Avoidance Beliefs Questionnaire (FABQ).
Scale of participant belief that they cannot do normal work until pain is treated, as part of the Fear-Avoidance Beliefs Questionnaire (FABQ).
Scale of participant belief that they will not be back to normal work within 3 months, as part of the Fear-Avoidance Beliefs Questionnaire (FABQ).
Scale of participant belief that they will never be able to go back to work, as part of the Fear-Avoidance Beliefs Questionnaire (FABQ).
Score of the total sum for fear-avoidance beliefs about work, as part of the Fear-Avoidance Beliefs Questionnaire (FABQ).
Score of the total sum for fear-avoidance beliefs about physical activity, as part of the Fear-Avoidance Beliefs Questionnaire (FABQ).
